# UI Protection Rule

## Critical: Do NOT Modify UI Without Explicit Request

**NEVER modify UI components, styling, layout, or visual elements unless the user explicitly requests UI changes.**

### Protected Elements

- Component structure and JSX markup
- Text content, labels, headings, placeholders
- Button text and UI copy
- Colors, spacing, fonts, visual styling
- Layout structure and component hierarchy
- Logo sizes, images, icons
- CSS classes and styling
- Form elements and their presentation

### What You CAN Do

- Fix bugs in logic (not UI appearance)
- Improve error handling and validation
- Add functionality that doesn't change existing UI
- Refactor code (preserving exact UI output)
- Update API routes and backend logic
- Fix TypeScript/linting errors
- Optimize performance

### When UI Changes Are Requested

1. Confirm the specific changes desired
2. Show a summary of proposed changes
3. Preserve all existing functionality
4. Test thoroughly

### Example Violations

❌ Changing button text from "Convert" to "Submit" without request
❌ Updating header text or styling
❌ Modifying logo size or positioning
❌ Restructuring component layout
❌ Changing colors or spacing

### Example Allowed Actions

✅ Improving error handling logic
✅ Adding API validation
✅ Fixing TypeScript errors
✅ Optimizing data fetching
✅ Refactoring code structure (same output)
